Sentencas: Intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells oxygen electrodes are modified by active interfacial layers.
Titulo: Improvement of Oxygen Electrode Performance of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Cells by Spray Pyrolysis Deposited Active Layers

Sentencas: Spray pyrolysis is used to produce thin (approximate to 500 nm) layers of mixed ionic and electronic conductors: Sm0.5Sr0.5CoO3-delta (SSC), La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta (LSC), La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF), and Pr6O11 (PrOx) on the electrode-electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Improvement of Oxygen Electrode Performance of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Cells by Spray Pyrolysis Deposited Active Layers

Sentencas: The influence of the annealing temperature on the electrode polarization (area specific resistance-ASR(pol)) is investigated by impedance spectroscopy of symmetrical electrodes in the temperature range of 400-700 degrees C.
Titulo: Improvement of Oxygen Electrode Performance of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Cells by Spray Pyrolysis Deposited Active Layers

Sentencas: The results show that the introduction of nanocrystalline interlayers promotes an oxygen reduction reaction by extending the active surface area and improved contact between the electrode and the electrolyte.
Titulo: Improvement of Oxygen Electrode Performance of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Cells by Spray Pyrolysis Deposited Active Layers

Sentencas: Introducing LSCF, LSC, or SSC interlayer reduces ASR(pol) by a factor of 4 and PrOx by a factor of 2 against the reference, powder processed LSCF electrode.
Titulo: Improvement of Oxygen Electrode Performance of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Cells by Spray Pyrolysis Deposited Active Layers

Sentencas: At 600 degrees C, the obtained ASR(pol) values for PrOx, LSCF, LSC, and SSC interlayer are 245, 137, 119, and 107 m ohm cm(2), which can be considered very low in comparison to standard powder processed oxygen electrodes.
Titulo: Improvement of Oxygen Electrode Performance of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Cells by Spray Pyrolysis Deposited Active Layers

Sentencas: Anode supported single cell with developed LSC/LSCF electrode reveals approximate to 1.2 W cm(-2) power output at 600 degrees C and maintains stable cell voltage of 0.75 V under 1 A cm(-2) during 60 h of the test.
Titulo: Improvement of Oxygen Electrode Performance of Intermediate Temperature Solid Oxide Cells by Spray Pyrolysis Deposited Active Layers
